"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The sns.heatmap function expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray, typically a 2D array or a DataFrame with numerical values. The 'tips' DataFrame contains categorical columns ('sex', 'smoker', 'day', 'time') which cannot be directly used in a heatmap. A suitable numerical aggregation or transformation of the data is required before passing it to sns.heatmap.\", \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.corr(), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"}"